It's unclear what led to the power outage that left motorists searching for routes around the 3.9 kilometre structure. CAPE TOWN - Western Cape Traffic officials have confirmed the Huguenot Tunnel near Worcester has been reopened. The tunnel was closed earlier today due to a power failure. Provincial Traffic Chief Kenny Africa says the tunnel was reopened in both directions at around 12:30pm on Saturday. It's unclear what led to the outage that left motorists searching for routes around the 3.9 kilometre structure. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)